<task id="R7-111" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire ITemplateEngine into PlaybookOrchestrationService + carry RunContext.NodeOutputs to subsequent nodes</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>11</wave>
    <estimated-effort>3-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, ai, refactoring, wave-11</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies .cs (PlaybookOrchestrationService + RunContext); tags include `bff-api`; has 7+ steps; downstream tasks 112/113/114/115 depend on this. FULL per task-execute Step 0.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>110</dependencies>
    <blocks>112, 113, 114</blocks>
    <fr-coverage>FR-15 (orchestrator now resolves node-output references — prerequisite for /narrate end-to-end)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace `PlaybookOrchestrationService.ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` literal `Replace` loop with
    `ITemplateEngine.Render`. Add `IDictionary&lt;string, object?&gt; NodeOutputs` to `RunContext`.
    After each node executes, register its OutputVariable → output value (use
    `TemplateEngine.ConvertJsonElement` for JsonElement results). Build the template context for
    each subsequent node from `RunContext.Parameters` + `RunContext.NodeOutputs` (merged dict).
    Preserve current `{{paramName}}` literal-substitution behavior — Handlebars handles those
    natively. Add unit tests proving (a) `{{paramName}}` still works, (b) `{{nodeName.field}}`
    now resolves, (c) missing/null references render as empty string (graceful per Handlebars
    config).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in C# generics, Handlebars.NET, and the BFF playbook
    orchestrator. Follow ADRs strictly. Match the existing TemplateEngine's "graceful on missing"
    contract — don't throw on unresolved bindings.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOrchestrationService` injects `ITemplateEngine`, calls `Render` (not literal Replace)
    against a merged Parameters + NodeOutputs context dict. `RunContext` carries `NodeOutputs`.
    Subsequent-node configJson resolution now sees prior nodes' OutputVariable values. xUnit
    tests prove behavior. Build passes; existing orchestrator tests pass (no regression).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="orchestrator">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="run-context">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookRunContext.cs</file>
    <file purpose="template-engine">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TemplateEngine.cs</file>
    <file purpose="template-engine-iface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ITemplateEngine.cs</file>
    <file purpose="executor-iface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="node-output">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/NodeOutput.cs</file>
    <file purpose="di-module">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs</file>
    <file purpose="design-from-110">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md</file>
    <file purpose="existing-tests">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationServiceTests.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — inject `ITemplateEngine` via constructor; do NOT new it up; no new abstraction layers introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — orchestrator stays a leaf service in the AI module; no public-contract surface changes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — single-task delta cap ≤ +2 MB compressed (wave 11 task 119 final gate). This task is C# only — no new packages, no new dependencies. Expected delta ~0.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — unit tests mock orchestrator collaborators minimally; use real ITemplateEngine (Handlebars-backed) in tests for end-to-end fidelity; ban Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt; / DI-registration / ctor null-check tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene checklist applies. State placement decision in commit body. Verify publish-size impact at Wave 11 task 119.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">No new component — extension of existing `PlaybookOrchestrationService` + `RunContext`. Component justification not required (modification only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="design-110">Follow the design doc's signatures + lifecycle. If implementation forces deviation, update the design doc first.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/playbook-orchestration</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
